In line with a UN campaign to modernize UN Compound facilities, the General Assembly in 2016 approved the renovation of Africa Hall, which was built in 1960/1961 and is the birthplace of the Organization of African Unity (OAU).&nbsp;A Swiss delegation met with Acting Executive Secretary of the Economic Commission for Africa (ECA), Abdalla Hamdok, to discuss Switzerland's support for the Africa Hall renovation project. Read&nbsp;more. More on the ECA in this&nbsp;BRIEFING.&nbsp;